uber - package uber
 
UberApp - Class in uber
UberApp connects the various methods and classes of the package into one cohesive program Represents the overall app connecting the Drivers and Passengers
UberApp() - Constructor for class uber.UberApp
 
UberAppTester - Class in tests
 
UberAppTester() - Constructor for class tests.UberAppTester
 
UberIO - Class in uber
Controls I/O for the Uber program Uses JSON Contains warning because of json.simple's lack of generics and use of raw types
UberIO() - Constructor for class uber.UberIO
 
UberIOTester - Class in tests
 
UberIOTester() - Constructor for class tests.UberIOTester
 
UberRunner - Class in uber
Main method that runs entire program
UberRunner() - Constructor for class uber.UberRunner
 
User - Class in uber
User of Uber is an abstract parent of Passenger and Driver
User(String, double) - Constructor for class uber.User
Constructor without Location inputs defaults to (0,0) Initializer lacks knowledge of Locations and of GRIDSIZE, can set later
User(String, Location, double) - Constructor for class uber.User
Constructor with Location for testing purposes
UsersList - Class in uber
UsersList is an enclosing class for Lists of Passenger and Driver Primarily implemented so initializer could pass both lists, also used for some of UberRunner's methods
UsersList(List<Passenger>, List<Driver>) - Constructor for class uber.UsersList
